fkans: SELECT DISTINCT pno FROM spj WHERE qty > (SELECT MAX(qty) FROM spj WHERE pno = 'p6')
SELECT maker FROM product, pc WHERE product.model = pc.model GROUP BY maker HAVING COUNT(*) = 3
SELECT students.sno, students.sname, sc.cno, sc.score FROM students LEFT JOIN sc ON students.sno = sc.sno
SELECT COUNT(*) FROM product WHERE PName LIKE '%螺母%'
SELECT MAX(Salary) AS max_Salary, MIN(Salary) AS min_Salary FROM employee
SELECT Wno, COUNT(Eid) AS Count_Eid FROM employee GROUP BY Wno
SELECT Eid, EName FROM employee WHERE Wno = 'A01' AND Salary > (SELECT MAX(Salary) FROM employee WHERE Wno = 'A02')
SELECT Sid FROM orders GROUP BY Sid HAVING SUM(QTY) = (SELECT MAX(total_qty) FROM (SELECT SUM(QTY) AS total_qty FROM orders GROUP BY Sid) AS temp)
SELECT DISTINCT e.Eid, e.EName FROM employee e, orders o WHERE e.Eid = o.Eid AND o.Pid IN (SELECT Pid FROM orders WHERE Eid = '0011') AND o.Eid != '0011'
SELECT p.maker FROM product p, pc c WHERE p.model = c.model AND c.ram = (SELECT MIN(ram) FROM pc) AND c.speed = (SELECT MAX(speed) FROM pc WHERE ram = (SELECT MIN(ram) FROM pc))

SELECT maker FROM (SELECT maker, type, COUNT(model) as model_count FROM product WHERE type IN ('PC', '便携式电脑') GROUP BY maker, type HAVING AVG((SELECT speed FROM pc WHERE pc.model = product.model)) >= 133 OR AVG((SELECT speed FROM laptop WHERE laptop.model = product.model)) >= 133) AS subquery GROUP BY maker HAVING SUM(model_count) >= 2 ORDER BY maker
SELECT Eid, EName FROM employee WHERE Wno = 'A01' AND Salary < (SELECT MAX(Salary) FROM employee WHERE Wno = 'A02')
SELECT dept, COUNT(*) AS student_count FROM student GROUP BY dept ORDER BY student_count DESC
SELECT sno, AVG(grade) FROM score GROUP BY sno HAVING COUNT(cno) >= 2
